Type casting - converting value of one type to another

2 types : widening/implicit/automatic
narrowing/explicit/manual

Conditional statement :
1. if statement
2.switch statement

if statement:
 Syntax:
 if(condition) {execute}

 --------------------------
 if(condition) {
 code A;
 } else {
 code B;
 }

 -------------------------------
 there more conditions to test

 if(condition){
 code A;
 } else if(Condition2) {
 code B;
 } else if(condition3) {
 code C;
 } else {
 code d;
 }

 else is optional, with IF program is running
 else we don't need condition

 -------------------------------

 Nested if, can be nested everywhere in statement
 nested is ; if inside another if

 why? when we have 1 condition depend on another
 how:

 if(condition) { ==> outer if

 if(condition) { ==>nested if
 }
 }

 nested if depend on outer if